# Qt changeEvent + setStyleSheet (Mandatory — No Startup Crash)

**Status:** Verified failure on Windows (2026-06). Calling `setStyleSheet()` (or `setPalette()` on self/children) from `changeEvent` on `QEvent::StyleChange` causes **infinite recursion → stack overflow `0xC00000FD`** — app exits silently after a few seconds with no window.

## Root cause

1. `changeEvent` handles `StyleChange` → calls `setStyleSheet()`
2. `setStyleSheet()` posts another `StyleChange`
3. Loop until stack overflow

Same risk when `setStyleSheet` runs inside a theme helper invoked from `StyleChange`. `PaletteChange` + child `setPalette` can also recurse unless guarded.

## Required pattern

| Do | Don't |
|----|--------|
| Call `setStyleSheet()` **once** in constructor / `setupUi` | Call `setStyleSheet()` from `changeEvent` on `StyleChange` |
| Use `palette(...)` in static stylesheet for theme-aware chrome | Re-apply full stylesheet on every palette/style change |
| On `PaletteChange` / `ApplicationPaletteChange` only: update label colors via `QPalette` with `m_updatingTheme` guard | Handle `StyleChange` in `changeEvent` when handler touches stylesheet or palette |
| Reference `TargetWindowDetailPanel`, `CustomTitleBar` | Add new widgets that refresh stylesheet from `changeEvent` without review |

## Safe changeEvent template

```cpp
void MyWidget::changeEvent(QEvent* event) {
    QFrame::changeEvent(event);
    switch (event->type()) {
    case QEvent::PaletteChange:
    case QEvent::ApplicationPaletteChange:
        updateThemeColors(); // must NOT call setStyleSheet; use guard if setPalette
        break;
    default:
        break;
    }
}
```

## Before merging UI theme work

- Grep for `StyleChange` + `setStyleSheet` / `applyTheme` in the same widget.
- Run `SuckbongMachine.exe` and confirm process stays alive >10 s (crash reproduces in ~3–6 s when broken).

